{"word":"ἱερεύς","slug":"ἱερεύς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἱερεύς</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἱερός'><el>ἱερός</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a priest, sacrificer</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, <el>ἱερεύς τις ἄτης</el> <i>a minister</i> of woe, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; and, comically, <el>λεπτοτάτων λήρων ἱερεῦ</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}